    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <add>ב"ה באלטימארע יום ב' ב"ה סיון תכ ב"ב</add>
            </p>
            <p>My Direction</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">A. Rice</persName>
                <placeName>133 E. Baltimore St.</placeName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName>, <date>Monday, 25 of Sivan
                    (June), 1862</date>.</p>
            <p>To my friend, the celebrated, etc., etc. <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Since I know very well that you, my friend, are ever ready to
                do<lb/> me a kindness, therefore I come to request of you one thing which may
                seem<lb/> little in your eyes but to me seems very difficult. Next week, I
                shall<lb/> have to make a wedding speech. The bride does not understand German<lb/>
                Therefore would you please be good enough to send me such a sermon<lb/> in English.
                It must, above all, contain that the Kallah must be<lb/> a Jewish life, and a hint
                to the wise, etc. Please write it very clear<lb/> so that I should be able to read
                it, and send me this by <date>Friday</date> or<lb/>
                <date>Saturday</date>. Since my house is too far from the synagogue, I am
                com<lb/>pelled to change my residence next week and, because of this, I am<lb/> very
                much occupied.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your true friend,</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham Rice</persName>
            </p>
            <p>My direction</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">A. Rice</persName>
                <placeName>133 E. Baltimore St.</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
